# Loan Approval Prediction Report

## 1. Project Overview

The objective of this project is to develop a machine learning model that predicts whether a loan application will be approved or rejected based on applicant information.

The project aims to assist financial institutions in making faster and more consistent loan approval decisions by analyzing historical applicant data.

A Random Forest classification model was trained and evaluated using a loan approval dataset.

---

## 2. Dataset Information

Dataset Name: Loan Approval Prediction

Total Records: 381

Total Features: 12

Target Variable: Loan_Status

Features Included:

* Gender
* Married
* Dependents
* Education
* Self_Employed
* ApplicantIncome
* CoapplicantIncome
* LoanAmount
* Loan_Amount_Term
* Credit_History
* Property_Area
* Loan_Status

---

## 3. Data Quality Assessment

The dataset was inspected for missing values and data quality issues before model training.

Missing values were identified in the following columns:

* Gender
* Dependents
* Self_Employed
* Loan_Amount_Term
* Credit_History

These missing values were handled during preprocessing to ensure data consistency.

---

## 4. Target Variable Analysis

The target variable was Loan_Status.

Class Distribution:

* Approved Loans (Y): 271
* Rejected Loans (N): 110

The dataset contains a higher proportion of approved loans compared to rejected loans.

---

## 5. Data Preprocessing

The following preprocessing techniques were applied:

### Missing Value Handling

* Numerical missing values were filled using Mean Imputation.
* Categorical missing values were filled using Most Frequent (Mode) Imputation.

### Feature Scaling

* StandardScaler was applied to numerical features.

### Data Preparation

The dataset was prepared for machine learning training after handling missing values and feature scaling.

---

## 6. Model Training

A Random Forest Classifier was used for model training.

The dataset was divided into training and testing subsets for evaluation.

The model was trained using the selected features and target variable.

---

## 7. Model Results

Model: Random Forest Classifier

Accuracy Score: 80.52%

Classification Performance:

Class N:

* Precision: 1.00
* Recall: 0.29
* F1-Score: 0.44

Class Y:

* Precision: 0.79
* Recall: 1.00
* F1-Score: 0.88

Overall Performance:

* Accuracy: 0.81
* Weighted F1 Score: 0.76

The model achieved satisfactory performance for loan approval prediction.

---

## 8. Business Recommendations

Based on the analysis and model results:

* Credit history appears to be a strong indicator of loan approval.
* Applicants with stronger financial profiles have a higher likelihood of approval.
* The model can be used as a preliminary screening tool for loan applications.
* Additional applicant information may further improve prediction performance.

---

## 9. Conclusion

A machine learning solution was successfully developed to predict loan approval outcomes.

The project included data analysis, preprocessing, model training, and evaluation.

The Random Forest model achieved an accuracy of 80.52% and demonstrated its ability to support loan approval decision-making processes.

This project demonstrates the practical application of machine learning techniques in financial risk assessment and loan approval prediction.
